00:59:05.920 --> 00:59:09.580
Your equity positions,
when you add up the equity

00:59:09.580 --> 00:59:14.840
positions, those portfolio
weights, you get 200%.

00:59:14.840 --> 00:59:20.410
But your riskless bonds,
you shorted $50,000.

00:59:20.410 --> 00:59:23.960
You're borrowing
$50,000 from the broker,

00:59:23.960 --> 00:59:25.930
so you've got minus 100%.

00:59:25.930 --> 00:59:30.080
When you add those two, you
get back 100%, or in this case,

00:59:30.080 --> 00:59:31.270
$50,000.

00:59:31.270 --> 00:59:34.450
So you start out
with $50,000 cash

00:59:34.450 --> 00:59:37.900
and then you buy
$100,000 worth of stocks

00:59:37.900 --> 00:59:42.590
by borrowing an extra
$50,000 from your broker.

00:59:42.590 --> 00:59:43.315
Yeah?

